Sample_treatment_protocol_ch1: Cell lines were treated with 10 µM enzalutamide (ENZ) or 10 μM GSK126, as indicated
Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: LNCaP, CRPC (16D), and enzalutamide (ENZ)-resistant tNEPC (42D, 42F) cell lines were cultured in RPMI-1640 media containing 10% fetal bovine serum, with the ENZ-resistant cell lines supplemented with 10 µmol/L ENZ. LASCPC-1 and NCI-H660 cell lines were cultured in HITES media, formulated as follows: RPMI-1640, 5% FBS, 10 nM hydrocortisone, 10 nM β-estradiol, 1x Insulin-Transferrin-Selenium, 1x GlutaMAX.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was isolated using the PureLink RNA Mini Kit (Thermo, #12183018A) following manufacturer’s procedure, Library constructions were performed using the NEBnext Ultra ii Stranded RNA Library Prep Kit. Sequencing was performed on an Illumina NextSeq 500 to generate 2x42-bp paired-end reads.
Sample_data_processing: For RNA-seq, data was de-multiplexed using bcl2fastq2 Conversion Software (version 2.20) and the resultant read sequences were aligned to the hg19 human reference genome using STAR aligner. Assembly and differential expression was estimated using Cufflinks software (version 2.2.1) available through the Illumina BaseSpace Sequence Hub. Expression levels (FPMK) were estimated by counting all nucleotides mapped to each gene and were normalized by the total number of mapped nucleotides (per million) and the gene length (per kb)., For ChIP-seq, reads were aligned to the hg38 human reference genome using BWA-MEM software (version 0.7.17) with default parameters. Alignments with quality less than 60 were filtered out (leaving only uniquely mapped reads) using Samtools software (version 1.9). Peaks were called using MACS2 (version 2.1.2) with FDR q-value , For ATAC-seq, reads were aligned to the hg38 human reference genome using BWA-MEM software (version 0.7.17) with default parameters. Reads with alignment quality less than 60 were filtered out using Samtools software (version 1.9). Peaks were called using MACS2 (version 2.1.2) with FDR q-value
Supplementary_files_format_and_content: For RNA-seq, tab-delimited files contain FPKM values for each sample. For ChIP-seq and ATAC-seq, bigWig files were generated using DeepTools bamCoverage command with bin size of 25.

LASCPC-1 and NCI-H660 cell lines were cultured in HITES media, formulated as follows: RPMI-1640, 5% FBS, 10 nM hydrocortisone, 10 nM β-estradiol, 1x Insulin-Transferrin-Selenium, 1x GlutaMAX.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Samples were processed for ATAC-seq as previously described (Buenrostro et al., 2013; Buenrostro et al., 2015), with some modification. Briefly, cells grown to 60-70% confluency were collected using CellStripper for 15 min at 24°C with orbital shaking and subsequent centrifugation at 2300 rpm for 5 min at 4°C. Cells were washed with pre-chilled 1x PBS, and 5 x 104 cells were lysed using 50 µl ATAC-seq lysis buffer [10 mM Tris-HCl (pH 7.4), 10 mM NaCl, 3 mM MgCl2, 0.1% IGEPAL CA-630 in 1x PBS] for 1 minute at 4°C. Nuclei were subsequently collected by centrifugation at 2300 rpm for 5 min at 4°C., Tagmentation reaction was performed using 2.5 µl Illumina TDE1 in 50 µl Illumina TD buffer at 37°C for 30 min. The tagmented DNA library was purified using the QIAquick PCR Purification Kit. Library quantification and number of amplification cycles was determined as described (Buenrostro et al., 2015). Sequencing was performed on an Illumina NextSeq 500 to generate 2x75-bp paired-end reads.
Sample_data_processing: For RNA-seq, data was de-multiplexed using bcl2fastq2 Conversion Software (version 2.20) and the resultant read sequences were aligned to the hg19 human reference genome using STAR aligner. Assembly and differential expression was estimated using Cufflinks software (version 2.2.1) available through the Illumina BaseSpace Sequence Hub. Expression levels (FPMK) were estimated by counting all nucleotides mapped to each gene and were normalized by the total number of mapped nucleotides (per million) and the gene length (per kb)., For ChIP-seq, reads were aligned to the hg38 human reference genome using BWA-MEM software (version 0.7.17) with default parameters. Alignments with quality less than 60 were filtered out (leaving only uniquely mapped reads) using Samtools software (version 1.9). Peaks were called using MACS2 (version 2.1.2) with FDR q-value , For ATAC-seq, reads were aligned to the hg38 human reference genome using BWA-MEM software (version 0.7.17) with default parameters. Reads with alignment quality less than 60 were filtered out using Samtools software (version 1.9). Peaks were called using MACS2 (version 2.1.2) with FDR q-value

Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: RNA was isolated using the PureLink RNA Mini Kit (Thermo, #12183018A)., Libraries were constructed using the NEBnext Ultra ii Stranded RNA Library Prep Kit.
Sample_data_processing: For RNAseq, Illumina Nextseq500 reads were demultiplexed using bcl2fastq. Alignment of reads to hg19 was performed using STAR aligner with the default setting in Illumina Basespace., For ChIPseq, reads were aligned to hg38 using BWA (v. 0.7.17). MACS2 was used for peak calling., For ChIP-seq, bigWig files were generated using deeptools (v. 2.5.4)
Supplementary_files_format_and_content: For RNA-seq, tab-delimited files contain FPKM values for each sample.
